passes.benefit_text:
Each pass admits two adults at $10 each for general admission and special exhibition and up to 4 children aged 7-17 at $10 each for special exhibition only.&nbsp; There is no discount for children 7-17 for general admission (currently $10) . Children 6 and under are admitted free.&nbsp;
The Museum of Fine Arts suggests reserving tickets prior to your visit. Once you reserve the museum pass through this website, you will receive a confirmation email with a promo-code.&nbsp; Use this code to reserve tickets on the MFA website or present it at the MFA admissions desk to receive your discount when you visit the museum.
For museum questions call the MFA customer service line at 1-800-440-6975.

This pass will admit up to 4 people at a 50% discount on tickets to the Museum’s Exhibit Halls. Children under 3 are not included in the count of 4 and are always admitted for free.&nbsp;
Your Library pass can only be used on the date printed on the pass.
Please bring your library pass confirmation (printed or displayed on a phone) when you visit.
When you arrive at the Museum, stop at the Box Office to exchange your library pass and purchase your Exhibit Hall tickets at the discounted rate. If you have any questions or would like to reserve your Exhibit Hall passes in advance to avoid waiting in line the day of your visit, please call 617-723-2500 (9 a.m. - 5 p.m. daily).
If you are unable to show your library confirmation on a phone, you may print out a copy using the link in the confirmation email or request a paper copy from the library.
Library: Gleason Public Library &nbsp;
